obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6688)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6688&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Commissions of`
  line `Inquiry Act, 1952.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line *****
  line ]
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 79 of 1971, s. 2, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. 1st October, 1952, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 1670, dated the 30th September, 1952, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3.`
  line
  line `This Act, as amended by Act 79 of 1971, came into force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir on 6-3-1972 and in the`
  line `districts of Kohima and Mokokchung in the State of Nagaland on 15-2-1972, vide notification No. 94(E), dated 4-3-1972`
  line `and 74(E), dated 14-2-1972, respectively, issued under s. 15 of Act 79 of 1972.`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6689)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6689&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government, in relation to a Commission appointed by it to make an`
  line `inquiry into any matter relatable to any of the entries enumerated in List I or List II or List III in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Government, in relation to a Commission appointed by it to make an inquiry`
  line `into any matter relatable to any of the entries enumerated in List II or List III in the Seventh`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution:`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(b) "Commission" means a Commission of Inquiry appointed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The Proviso omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide`
  line `notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (6690)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to laws not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6690&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `2A. [Construction of references to laws not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir^*.]--`
  line `omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide`
  line `notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation`
  line `(Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6691)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6691&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, if it is of opinion that it`
  line `is necessary so to do, and shall if a resolution in this behalf is passed by ^1`
  line `[each House of Parliament`
  line `or, as the case may be, the Legislature of the State], by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a`
  line `Commission of Inquiry for the purpose of making an inquiry into any definite matter of public`
  line `importance and performing such functions and within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, and the Commission so appointed shall make the inquiry and perform the functions`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such Commission has been appointed to inquire into any matter--`
  line
  line `(a) by the Central Government, no State Government shall, except with the approval of the`
  line `Central Government, appoint another Commission to inquire into the same matter for so long as`
  line `the Commission appointed by the Central Government is functioning;`
  line
  line `(b) by a State Government, the Central Government shall not appoint another Commission to`
  line `inquire into the same matter for so long as the Commission appointed by the State Government is`
  line `functioning, unless the Central Government is of opinion that the scope of the inquiry should be`
  line `extended to two or more States.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may consist of one or more members appointed by the appropriate`
  line `Government, and where the Commission consists of more than one member, one of them may be`
  line `appointed as the Chairman thereof.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) The appropriate Government , at any stage of an inquiry by the Commission fill any vacancy which may have arisen in the office of a member of the Commission (whether consisting of`
  line `one or more than one member).`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government shall cause to be laid before ^1[each House of Parliament or, as the case may be, the Legislature of the State], the report, if any, of the Commission on the inquiry`
  line `made by the Commission under sub-section (1) together with a memorandum of the action taken`
  line `thereon, within a period of six months of the submission of the report by the Commission to the`
  line `appropriate Government.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `**** *`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1990, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-8-1990).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-sections (5) and (6) omitted by Act 19 of 1990, s. 2, ibid.(w.e.f. 28-8-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6692)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6692&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall have the powers of a civil court, while trying`
  line `a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a)`
  line `^1[summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India] and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6693)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Additional powers of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 7 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6693&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the appropriate Government is of opinion`
  line `that, having regard to the nature of the inquiry to be made and other circumstances of the case, all or`
  line `any of the provisions of sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) should`
  line `be made applicable to a Commission, the appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that all or such of the said provisions as may be specified in the notification shall apply`
  line `to that Commission and on the issue of such a notification, the said provisions shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have power to require any person, subject to any privilege which may`
  line `be claimed by that person under any law for the time being in force, to furnish information on such`
  line `points or matters as, in the opinion of the Commission, may be useful for, or relevant to, the`
  line `subject matter of the inquiry ^1`
  line `[and any person so required shall be deemed to be legally bound to`
  line `furnish such information within the meaning of section 176 and section 177 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860)].`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission or any officer, not below the rank of a Gazetted Officer, specially authorised`
  line `in this behalf by the Commission may enter any building or place where the Commission has reason`
  line `to believe that any books of account or other documents relating to the subject matter of the inquiry`
  line `may be found, and may seize any books of account or documents or take extracts or copies therefrom,`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 102 and section 103 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898`
  line `(5 of 1898), in so far as they may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court and when any offence as is described in`
  line `section 175, section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 228 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) is committed in the view or presence of the Commission, the Commission may, after`
  line `recording the facts constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as provided for in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), forward the case to a magistrate having jurisdiction to`
  line `try the same and the magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the`
  line `complaint against the accused as if the case had been forwarded to him under section 482 of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1898.`
  line
  line `(5) Any proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (6694)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Commission to utilise the services of certain officers and investigation agencies for conducting investigation pertaining to inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6694&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[5A. Power of Commission to utilise the services of certain officers and investigation`
  line `agencies for conducting investigation pertaining to inquiry.--(1) The Commission may, for the`
  line `purpose of conducting any investigation pertaining to the inquiry, utilise the services,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a Commission appointed by the Central Government, of any officer or`
  line `investigation agency of the Central Government or any State Government with the concurrence of`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Commission appointed by the State Government, of any officer or`
  line `investigation agency of the State Government or Central Government with the concurrence of the`
  line `State Government or the Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of investigating into any matter pertaining to the inquiry, any officer or`
  line `agency whose services are utilised under sub-section (1) may, subject to the direction and control of`
  line `the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) summon and enforce the attendance of any person and examine him;`
  line
  line `(b) require the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) requisition any public record or copy thereof from any office.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 6 shall apply in relation to any statement made by a person before`
  line `any officer or agency whose services are utilised under sub section (1) as they apply in relation to any`
  line `statement made by a person in the course of giving evidence before the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer or agency, whose services are utilised under sub-section (1), shall investigate into`
  line `any matter pertaining to the inquiry and submit a report thereon (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `the investigation report) to the Commission within such period as may be specified by the`
  line `Commission in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall satisfy itself about the correctness of the facts stated and the`
  line `conclusions, if any, arrived at in the investigation report submitted to it under sub-section (4), and for`
  line `this purpose the Commission may make such inquiry (including the examination of the person or`
  line `persons who conducted or assisted in the investigation) as it thinks fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (6695)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of Commission to appoint assessors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 63 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6695&sectionno=5B&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[5B. Power of Commission to appoint assessors.The Commission may, for the purpose of`
  line `conducting any inquiry, appoint persons having special knowledge of any matter connected with the`
  line `inquiry as assessors, to assist and advise the Commission in the inquiry and the assessors shall be`
  line `entitled to such travelling and other expenses as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6696)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 9
  title `Statements made by persons to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6696&sectionno=6&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No statement made by a person in the`
  line `course of giving evidence before the Commission shall subject him to, or be used against him in, any`
  line `civil or criminal proceeding except a prosecution for giving false evidence by such statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement—`
  line
  line `(a) is made in reply to a question which he is required by the Commission to answer, or`
  line
  line `(b) is relevant to the subject matter of the inquiry`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (6697)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 10
  title `Persons not obliged to disclose secret process of manufacture of goods in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 9 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6697&sectionno=6A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[6A. Persons not obliged to disclose secret process of manufacture of goods in certain`
  line `cases.--Except in cases where a Commission is expressly required to inquire into the process of`
  line `manufacture of any goods, nothing in this Act shall be deemed to compel any person giving evidence`
  line `before the Commission to disclose any secret process of manufacture thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6698)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 11
  title `Commission to cease to exist when so notified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6698&sectionno=7&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[7. Commission to cease to exist when so notified.--(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare that--`
  line
  line `(a) a Commission (other than a Commission appointed in pursuance of a resolution passed by`
  line ^2
  line `[each House of Parliament or, as the case may be, the Legislature of the State] shall cease to`
  line `exist, if it is of opinion that the continued existence of the Commission is unnecessary;`
  line
  line `(b) a Commission appointed in pursuance of a resolution passed by ^2`
  line `[each House of`
  line `Parliament or, as the case may be, the Legislature of the State] shall cease to exist if a resolution`
  line `for the discontinuance of the Commission is passed by ^2`
  line `[each House of Parliament or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Legislature of the State].`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall specify the date from which the`
  line `Commission shall cease to exist and on the issue of such notification, the Commission shall cease to`
  line `exist with effect from the date specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 7 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 19 of 1990, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-8-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6699)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure to be followed by the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by Act 79 of 1971, s. 11 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6699&sectionno=8&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall, subject to any rules`
  line `that may be made in this behalf, have power to regulate its own procedure (including the fixing of`
  line `places and times of its sittings and deciding whether to sit in public or in private) ^1`
  line `* * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (6700)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 13
  title `Inquiry not to be interrupted by reason of vacancy or change in the constitution of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 12, ibid (w.e.f. 30-10-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6700&sectionno=8A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Inquiry not to be interrupted by reason of vacancy or change in the constitution of the`
  line `Commission.--(1) Where the Commission consists of two or more members, it may act notwithstanding the absence of the Chairman or any other member or any vacancy among its`
  line members.
  line
  line `(2) Where during the course of an inquiry before a Commission, a change has taken place in the`
  line `constitution of the Commission by reason of any vacancy having been filled or by any other reason, it`
  line `shall not be necessary for the Commission to commence the inquiry a fresh and the inquiry may be`
  line `continued from the stage at which the change took place.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (6701)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 14
  title `Persons likely to be prejudicially affected to be heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-10-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6701&sectionno=8B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Persons likely to be prejudicially affected to be heard.--If, at any stage of the inquiry, the`
  line Commission,--
  line
  line `(a) considers it necessary to inquire into the conduct of any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of opinion that the reputation of any person is likely to be prejudicially affected by the`
  line inquiry,
  line
  line `the Commission shall give to that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the inquiry and to`
  line `produce evidence in his defence:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply where the credit of a witness is being impeached.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_c:
  sectionId (6702)
  sectionNo 8C
  orderNo 15
  title `Right of cross-examination and representation by legal practitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-10-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6702&sectionno=8C&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[8C. Right of cross-examination and representation by legal practitioner.--The appropriate`
  line `Government, every person referred to in section 8B and, with the permission of the Commission, any`
  line `other person whose evidence is recorded by the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) may cross-examine a witness other than a witness produced by it or him;`
  line
  line `(b) may address the Commission; and`
  line
  line `(c) may be represented before the Commission by a legal practitioner or, with the permission`
  line `of the Commission, by any other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6703)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6703&sectionno=9&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the appropriate Government, the Commission or any member thereof, or any person acting under the`
  line `direction either of the appropriate Government or of the Commission in respect of anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or orders made`
  line `thereunder or in respect of the publication, by or under the authority of the appropriate Government or`
  line `the Commission, of any report, paper or proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6704)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 17
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6704&sectionno=10&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Commission and every officer`
  line `appointed or authorised by the Commission in exercise of functions under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (6705)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 18
  title `Penalty for acts calculated to bring the Commission or any member thereof into disrepute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6705&sectionno=10A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[10A. Penalty for acts calculated to bring the Commission or any member thereof into`
  line `disrepute.--(1) If any person, by words either spoken or intended to be read, makes or publishes any`
  line `statement or does any other act, which is calculated to bring the Commission or any member thereof`
  line `into disrepute, he shall be punishable with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line `when an offence under sub-section (1) is alleged to have been committed, the High Court may take`
  line `cognizance of such offence, without the case being committed to it, upon a complaint in writing, made`
  line `by a member of a Commission or an officer of the Commission authorised by it in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every complaint referred to it in sub-section (2) shall set forth the facts which constitute the`
  line `offence alleged, the nature of such offence and such other particulars as are reasonably sufficient to`
  line `give notice to the accused of the offence alleged to have been committed by him.`
  line
  line `(4) No High Court shall take cognizance of an offence under sub-section (1) unless the complaint`
  line `is made within six months from the date on which the offence is alleged to have been committed.`
  line
  line `(5) A High Court taking cognizance of an offence under sub-section (1) shall try the case in`
  line `accordance with the procedure for the trial of warrant cases instituted otherwise than on a police`
  line `report before a court of a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the personal attendance of a member of a Commission as a complainant or`
  line `otherwise is not required in such trial.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) an`
  line `appeal shall lie as a matter of right from any judgment of the High Court to the Supreme Court, both`
  line `on facts and on law.`
  line
  line `(7) Every appeal to the Supreme Court under sub-section (6) shall be preferred within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of the judgment appealed from:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `the period of thirty days.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 13 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 63 of 1988, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 10-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6706)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 19
  title `Act to apply to other inquiring authorities in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6706&sectionno=11&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where any authority (by`
  line `whatever name called), other than a Commission appointed under section 3, has been or is set up`
  line `under any resolution or order of the appropriate Government for the purpose of making an inquiry`
  line `into any definite matter of public importance and that Government is of opinion that all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act should be made applicable to that authority, that Government may, subject to`
  line `the prohibition contained in the proviso to sub section (1) of section 3, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that the said provisions of this Act shall apply to that authority, and on the issue of`
  line `such a notification, that authority shall be deemed to be a Commission appointed under section 3 for`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6707)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316&sectionId=6707&sectionno=12&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00004_195260_1517807319316
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office and the conditions of service of the members of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which inquiries may be held under this Act and the procedure to be`
  line `followed by the Commission in respect of the proceedings before it;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers of civil court which may be vested in the Commission;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(cc) the travelling and other expenses payable to assessors appointed under section 5B, and`
  line `to person summoned by the Commission to give evidence or to produce documents before it;]`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or ^3`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 63 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 10-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2 .Ins. by Act 79 of 1971, s. 14 (w.e.f. 30-12-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
